next108 annotation text;}{\s109\li560\sa40\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tldot\tx6960\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \sbasedon110 \snext109 toc 3;}{\s110\sa40\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tldot\tx6960\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \sbasedon0 \snext111 toc 1;}{\s111\li280\sa40\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tldot\tx6960\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \sbasedon110 \snext111 toc 2;}{\s112\sl140\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpg\phpg\posx1999\posy14702\adjustright \fs10\cgrid \sbasedon0 \snext112 footer;}{\s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid \sbasedon0 \snext59 header;}{\s114\li280\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \sbasedon0 \snext114 Normal Indent;}{\s115\fi-280\li560\ri280\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx560\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \sbasedon97 \snext97 SbrLp;}{\s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid \snext116 BodyText;}}{\*\revtbl {Unknown;}}{\info{\title  }{\subject  }{\author Microsoft Corp}{\keywords  }{\doccomm  }{\operator Regis Brid}{\creatim\yr1996\mo12\dy13\hr8\min43}{\revtim\yr1997\mo9\dy4\hr14\min53}{\printim\yr1996\mo12\dy13\hr8\min26}{\version4}{\edmins2}{\nofpages39}{\nofwords6919}{\nofchars39443}{\*\company ActiveX CUE, Microsoft Corp.}{\nofcharsws48438}{\vern71}}\margl3330\margr1530\margt-2540\margb-2220\gutter420 \facingp\deftab274\widowctrl\ftnbj\aenddoc\noextrasprl\prcolbl\cvmme\sprsspbf\brkfrm\swpbdr\lytprtmet\linkstyles\hyphcaps0\viewkind4\viewscale100\pgbrdrhead\pgbrdrfoot \fet0\sectd \binfsxn1\binsxn1\sbkodd\linex0\headery1990\footery360\colsx0\endnhere\titlepg\sectdefaultcl {\headerl \pard\plain \s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid {\field{\*\fldinst {PAGE}}{\fldrslt {\lang1024 2}}}{\expnd50\expndtw250   }{
\par }\pard\plain \s59\li-1770\ri30\sb50\sl-80\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }}{\headerr \pard\plain \s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid {\tab Microsoft Chat Control Visual Basic Overview}{\expnd50\expndtw250   }{\field{\*\fldinst {PAGE}}{\fldrslt {\lang1024 3}}}{
\par }\pard\plain \s59\li-1770\ri30\sb50\sl-80\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }}{\headerf \pard\plain \s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid {\tab }{\field{\*\fldinst {PAGE}}{\fldrslt {\lang1024 39}}}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s59\li-1770\ri30\sb50\sl-80\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }}{\*\pnseclvl1\pnucrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl2\pnucltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl3\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl4\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl5\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl6\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl7\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl8\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}\pard\plain \s43\sl-540\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phmrg\posnegx-1801\posy0\absh-2460\absw6720\nowrap\adjustright \b\f16\fs48\cgrid {\f1 Microsoft Chat Control Visual Basic Overview
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Introduction
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The Microsoft® Chat control, which is an ActiveX™-based control, allows the user to participate in a chat, or conversation, that can communicate both text and data between two or more users connected to a chat server. The Chat control provides a default user interface that is completely customizable, or a custom user interface can be designed using the Chat control to implement it. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {Microsoft Visual Basic® Scripting Edition (VBScript) can be used to insert the Chat control into the HTML that creates a site on the World Wide Web (WWW or Web), or the Chat control can be used in a Microsoft Visual Basic application program to create a chat client. Both implementations enable conversations between multiple users on client computers accessing a common chat server over the Internet. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Software Requirements 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {To implement Web pages that use the Chat control, the Web server must have access to a chat server. The Chat control enables the connection from the user's computer to a chat channel, or chat room, on the chat server. For information on installing and configuring a chat server, see the }{\i Internet Chat Server Operations Guide}{. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 User Interface 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The Chat control allows a variety of user interface options. The control has a user interface that can be configured, or a custom user interface can be created using the control's automation interface to implement it. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {The user interface provided with the Chat control is very flexible and can contain up to three panes in a single window. It includes a History text box, a Participant list box, a Send text box that provides space to type outgoing messages, a Send button, and a Whisper button. The Chat control can be set to allow users to resize the internal user interface (if it is being used). 
\par To broadcast a message, the user clicks in the Send text box, types the text of the message, and clicks the Send button on the toolbar. To whisper to specific members of the chat room, a user can select the names of the members in the Participant list box, click in the Send text box, type the message, and click the Whisper button. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Installation 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The Chat control can be installed from the Web or can be included with a Visual Basic application program. 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\li-1800\sb140\sa60\sl-380\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel1\adjustright \b\f16\fs34\cgrid {\f1 Installation from the Web 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Before users can take part in a conversation implemented with the Chat control, the control and certain supporting files must reside on the users' local computers. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {When you include the control in a Web page, you can use the HTML OBJECT tag to download the control and the dynamic-link libraries (DLLs) that it depends on. 
\par For example, the following lines inserted in a Web page cause the Chat control to be downloaded. Please note that the version in the }{\b CODEBASE=}{ line is subject to change and should be updated to the current version of the control that is available. 
\par }\pard\plain \s44\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\adjustright \f17\fs16\cgrid {\f2 <OBJECT
\par }\pard \s44\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\adjustright {\f2 STANDBY="Downloading the Microsoft Chat control"
\par CODETYPE="application/x-oleobject"
\par CLASSID="clsid:D6526FE0-E651-11CF-99CB-00C04FD64497"
\par CODEBASE="MSChatOCX.Cab#Version=4,71,206,0"
\par WIDTH=600
\par HEIGHT=350
\par ID=Chat>
\par <PARAM NAME="UIOption"   VALUE="4095">
\par <PARAM NAME="Appearance" VALUE="0">
\par <PARAM NAME="BorderStyle" VALUE="0">
\par <PARAM NAME="BackColor"  VALUE="255">
\par </OBJECT>
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\li-1800\sb140\sa60\sl-380\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel1\adjustright \b\f16\fs34\cgrid {\f1 Installation with a Visual Basic or Other Program 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {If the Chat control is used in a Visual Basic program or another OLE container, the Microsoft Visual Basic Setup Wizard can be used to create a setup program to install the control and the DLLs it requires. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Chat Control Rules
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The following rules apply to the use of the Chat control: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\fi-280\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx280\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The user will not get the }{\b OnMessage}{ event, if the message was sent by that user. However, if the internal user interface is used, the user will get the }{\b OnTextMessageSent}{ event. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab If a critical error occurs while chatting, the user will automatically be ejected from the chat room. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The }{\b BorderStyle}{ and }{\b Appearance}{ properties should be set only at startup time. They should not be changed in the middle of a conversation, because the content of the controls (text boxes and list boxes) would be lost. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The user cannot ignore herself or himself or a host. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab Only a host can change somebody into a spectator, participant, or host. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The host cannot change an ignored member into a host (the Ignore status must be removed first). 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The user cannot change the no whisper status of another user. 
\par }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {SYMBOL 183 \\f "Symbol" \\s 9.5 \\h }}{\fldrslt }}{\tab The user cannot change herself or himself into a spectator, participant, or host. 
\par }\pard\plain \s40\qr\sl-160\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }\pard \s40\qr\sl-160\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\sect }\sectd \binfsxn1\binsxn1\sbkodd\linex0\headery1990\footery360\colsx0\endnhere\titlepg\sectdefaultcl {\headerl \pard\plain \s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid {\field{\*\fldinst {PAGE}}{\fldrslt {\lang1024 36}}}{\expnd50\expndtw250   }{
\par }\pard\plain \s59\li-1770\ri30\sb50\sl-80\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }}{\headerr \pard\plain \s113\li-1800\sl-210\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx6960\adjustright \b\f1\fs19\cgrid {\tab Microsoft Chat Control Visual Basic Reference}{\expnd50\expndtw250   }{\field{\*\fldinst {PAGE}}{\fldrslt {\lang1024 37}}}{
\par }\pard\plain \s59\li-1770\ri30\sb50\sl-80\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }}\pard\plain \s43\sl-540\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phmrg\posnegx-1801\posy0\absh-2460\absw6720\nowrap\adjustright \b\f16\fs48\cgrid {\f1 Microsoft Chat Control Visual Basic Reference
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Introduction
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The Microsoft® Chat control is an ActiveX™-based control that provides the capability to create a chat, or conversation, that communicates text and/or data between two or more users connected through the Internet or an intranet. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {The following document is a reference that contains the properties, methods, events, and error codes associated with using the Chat control in a Microsoft Visual Basic® or Microsoft Visual Basic Scripting Edition (VBScript) application. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Properties 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This section covers the properties associated with the Microsoft Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v Appearance Property}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 Appearance Property 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Returns or sets the appearance of the Chat control. This property is persistent and is read-only when connected to a chat room. The }{\b Appearance}{ property has meaning only if the internal user interface is displayed. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .Appearance}{[}{\b =}{\i value}{]\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i value}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Optional. A short integer expression that determines the appearance of the Chat control. Can be set to one of the return values listed below. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Return Values
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Returns a short integer value that indicates the current appearance of the Chat control. Can be one of the following values. 
