\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i value}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Optional. A short integer expression that equals the sum of the desired user interface option values. Can include the following option values. 
\par }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s85\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Value \cell }\pard\plain \s37\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Description \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {1 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to display the Send button. Must set the Send text box (}{\i value}{=16) in order to set the Send button. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {2 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to display the Whisper button. Must set the Send button (}{\i value}{=1) in order to set the Whisper button. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {4 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to display the Participant list box. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {8 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to display the History text box. This window displays all messages that have been received. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {16 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to display the Send text box. This text box is where the user composes messages before sending them. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {32 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow members to be notified in the History text box when a new user joins the chat. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {64 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow members to be notified in the History text box when a user leaves the chat. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {128 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow the Chat control to display a dialog box that notifies the user when a member's status (host, participant, or spectator) changes, when a member's alias (nickname) changes, and when the user has been kicked by a host. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {256 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to insert a blank line between messages in the History text box. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {512 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow the Chat control to display error dialog boxes. When an }{\b OnError}{ event is triggered, a dialog box containing the error message will appear. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {1024 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow the user to resize the control. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {2048 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Set this value to allow any URLs appearing in the History text box to be clickable. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s103\qr\sl-140\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Return Values
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Returns the sum of the option values currently selected. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {To set a Chat control's user interface so that it includes a Send text box, Send button, Whisper button, History text box, and Participant list box, the }{\b UIOption}{ property must be set to the sum of the option values. In this case, the sum would equal 31 (16 + 1 + 2 + 8 + 4 = 31). To set the control to have all options, the sum would equal 4095 (1 + 2 + 4 + 8 + 16 + 32 + 64 + 128 + 256 + 512 + 1024 + 2048 = 4095). 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v Width Property}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 Width Property 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Returns or sets the width of the control in HiMetrics. Each HiMetrics unit corresponds to 0.01 mm. This property is persistent. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .Width}{[}{\b =}{\i value}{]\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i value}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Optional. A HiMetrics value that indicates the width of the Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Return Values
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Returns the current width of the Chat control in HiMetrics units. 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\li-1800\sb200\sa80\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\cgrid {\f1 Methods 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This section covers the methods associated with the Microsoft Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v AboutBox Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 AboutBox Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Displays the About message dialog box. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .AboutBox}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v BanParticipant Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 BanParticipant Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Bans a member from or reinstates a member to a chat room. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .BanParticipant}{ }{\i Name}{\b ,}{ }{\i Set}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Name}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A BSTR value that contains the alias of the member to be banned or reinstated. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Set}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A Boolean value that determines whether the member is banned or reinstated. If the value is set to TRUE, the member is banned from the chat room and cannot rejoin it. If the value is set to FALSE, the member is reinstated and can join the chat at any time. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The }{\b BanParticipant}{ method only prevents the member from rejoining or allows the member to rejoin the chat room after leaving or being kicked. This method does not kick the member from the chat room. }{\b BanParticipant}{ cannot be called before the }{\b OnEndEnumeration}{ event has been triggered. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v CancelEntering Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 CancelEntering Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Cancels an }{\b EnterRoom}{ operation 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .CancelEntering}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This method should be called only when the control's }{\b State}{ property is equal to 2 (Connecting). 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v ClearHistory Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 ClearHistory Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Empties the History text box. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .ClearHistory}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This method has an effect only if the value of }{\b UIOption}{ includes a History text box (}{\i value}{=8). 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v EnterRoom Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 EnterRoom Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Allows the user to enter the specified chat room. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .EnterRoom}{ }{\i RoomPath}{\b ,}{ }{\i RoomPwd}{\b ,}{ }{\i ThisParticipantAlias}{\b ,}{ }{\i SecurityPackage}{\b ,}{ }{\i Flags}{\b ,}{ }{\i Type}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i RoomPath}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A string value containing the location of the chat room. The format of the string should be: 
\par }\pard\plain \s50\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tqr\tx160\tx280\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {[}{\i prefix:}{]//}{\i server-name}{[:}{\i port-number}{]/[[#]|[&]]}{\i room-name}{ 
\par The }{\i prefix}{ is optional and can be either mic or irc. The }{\i server-name}{ is the host name of the chat server computer. The optional number sign (#) indicates that the chat room can be a global IRC room. The optional ampersand (&) indicates that the room can be a local IRC or MIC room. The }{\i room-name}{ is the name of the chat room. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i RoomPwd}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A string containing the room password or the host key used when creating or joining a password-protected room. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i ThisParticipantAlias}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A string containing the alias that the user will be known by in the chat room. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i SecurityPackage}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A string containing a list of security packages that are separated by semicolons and ordered by preference. If }{\i SecurityPackage}{ is set to an empty string, the control asks the server for a list of security packages it provides. If the server replies no packages at all, an anonymous connection is tried. If the server replies with a list of packages, the first package on the list is tried. If the string is set to "ALL", all the server's security packages are tried in an order defined by the server. The control will stop looping through the security packages as soon as one package succeeds or an error not related to the account information occurs. If all packages fail, the control will try to connect the user anonymously. The "ANON" string can be used to request anonymous connections. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Flags}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A combination of values used when creating or joining a room. These values characterize the room type and cannot change dynamically once the room is created. Set to zero to use no flags. Can be any combination of the following values. 
\par }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s85\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Value \cell }\pard\plain \s37\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Description \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {1 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Join an existing chat room or create a chat room if one does not exist. If this flag is not set, the }{\b EnterRoom}{ method will create a chat, but will not join an existing chat. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {2 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {The chat room will not be exposed to other servers on the Internet. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {4 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {The chat room is set up as read-only for news feeds, stock quotes, and so on. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {8 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {The chat room will allow only MIC clients to join it. IRC users will not be able to join the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {16 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {The server will accept only authenticated members in this chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {32 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Only authenticated members can talk in the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s103\qr\sl-140\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Type}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A combination of values to set the type of chat room. Set to zero to use no flags. The chat room type can dynamically vary during its lifetime. The user is notified when the room type changes via the }{\b OnRoomTypeChanged}{ event. Can be any combination of the following values. 
\par }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s85\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Value \cell }\pard\plain \s37\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \b\fs19\cgrid {Description \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {1 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Allows any user into the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {2 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Allows only hosts to change the topic of the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {4 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Allows only users who logged on to this server to enter the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {8 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Disables whispering in the chat room. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {16 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Creates an auditorium room. The member list shows only the user and the hosts. Participants cannot whisper, but hosts can whisper to anybody, regardless of whether the no whisper (}{\i Type}{=8) flag is set. Messages coming from participants are sent only to the hosts. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\trowd \trleft280 \clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx3160\clvertalt\cltxlrtb \cellx6960\pard\plain \s82\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {32 \cell }\pard\plain \s38\li240\sb20\sa60\sl-220\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\tx280\tx560\adjustright \fs19\cgrid {Creates a moderated room. Members join the chat room as spectators by default. \cell }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\intbl\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\row }\pard\plain \s103\qr\sl-140\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs12\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This method should be called only when the control's }{\b State}{ property is equal to 1 (Disconnected). 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v ExitRoom Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 ExitRoom Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Disconnects the user from the current chat room. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .ExitRoom}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {This method should be called only when the control's }{\b State}{ property is equal to 3 (Connected). 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v GetParticipantRealName Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 GetParticipantRealName Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Gets the real name of a participant by using the member's participant ID or alias (nickname). 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .GetParticipantRealName}{ }{\i ParticipantID}{\b ,}{ }{\i Alias}{\b ,}{ }{\i Synchronous}{\b ,}{ }{\i RealName}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i ParticipantID}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A long integer value that indicates which member's real name is being requested. If }{\i ParticipantID}{ is set to -1, the method uses the participant ID of the member selected in the Participant list box. If }{\i ParticipantID}{ is not set to -1, the participant ID must have come from an }{\b OnEnterParticipant}{ event. This value must be set to zero if the application is requesting the real name by using the member's alias. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Alias}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A BSTR value that contains the requested member's alias. This value must be set to an empty string if the application is requesting the real name by using the member's }{\i ParticipantID}{. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Synchronous}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A Boolean value that indicates whether this method is executed synchronously or asynchronously. If }{\i Synchronous}{ is set to TRUE, the real name is put into the string that is pointed to by }{\i RealName}{ for a Visual Basic or C/C++ application. If }{\i Synchronous}{ is set to FALSE, the answer to the query comes back asynchronously. If the query is successful, the }{\b OnParticipantRealName}{ event returns the information. If the query is not successful, the }{\b OnError}{ event is triggered. VBScript does not support pointers, so }{\i Synchronous}{ must be set to FALSE. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i RealName}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An address of a string where the real name of the member will be stored if the method is executed synchronously. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {When using }{\i ParticipantID}{, the scope of the search is limited to members currently in the chat room. When using }{\i Alias}{, the entire server is searched. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v InviteParticipant Method}}}{\v0\f1 
\par }\pard\plain \s71\li-1770\ri30\sb280\sa250\sl-120\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brdrcf2 \adjustright \fs8\cf8\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s60\li-1800\sa180\sl-440\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\tx0\adjustright \b\f16\fs40\up6\cgrid {\f1 InviteParticipant Method 
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {Invites a member to the user's current chat room. 
\par }\pard \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\i object}{\b .InviteParticipant}{ }{\i Alias}{\line 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Parts
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i object}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. An object expression that evaluates to a Chat control. 
\par }\pard\plain \s64\sl-240\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\cgrid {\i Alias}{ 
\par }\pard\plain \s65\li280\sa80\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {Required. A string value that contains the alias of the member to invite. 
\par }\pard\plain \s61\sb20\sl-220\slmult0\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\pvpara\phpg\posy0\absw1560\dxfrtext240\dfrmtxtx240\dfrmtxty240\adjustright \b\f16\fs21\cgrid {\f1 Remarks
\par }\pard\plain \s116\sa160\sl-240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \fs21\lang1024\cgrid {The member must be on the same chat server as the user. 
\par }\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\pard\plain \s88\sa80\keepn\nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright \v\f16\cf5\cgrid {\xe {\v KickParticipant Method}}}{\v0\f1 
